---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Base title="Conversational Guidance | Enhanced Task Completion">
  <article class="scenario">
    <div class="container">
      <a href={base} class="back">&larr; All scenarios</a>

      <header class="scenario__header">
        <span class="badge badge--primary">Slot-Filling</span>
        <h1>Conversational Guidance</h1>
        <p class="scenario__lead">
          The user gives fuzzy, incomplete info. The agent reasons through it, calls the right tools,
          and asks targeted follow-up questions — only for the details it can't figure out on its own.
        </p>
      </header>

      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Follow along</h2>
        <p>Open the chat UI in another tab, then follow each step below.</p>

        <div class="turn">
          <div class="turn__label">Step 1</div>
          <div class="turn__you">
            <span class="turn__who">You say:</span>
            <div class="try-prompt">
              <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">I want to return something. I'm Emily Chen, I think the order was 104-something from around April 14</blockquote>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="turn__expect">
            <span class="turn__who">The agent:</span>
            <ul>
              <li>Extracts the name "Emily Chen" and the fuzzy order hint "104-something, April 14"</li>
              <li>Calls <code>search_orders</code> to find Emily's orders</li>
              <li>Matches the fuzzy info to <strong>ORD-10478</strong> ($299, April 14)</li>
              <li>Calls <code>get_order</code> to pull the full details</li>
              <li>Shows the item (ErgoMax Office Chair) and asks: <em>"What's the reason for the return?"</em></li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="turn">
          <div class="turn__label">Step 2</div>
          <div class="turn__you">
            <span class="turn__who">You say:</span>
            <div class="try-prompt">
              <blockquote class="try-prompt__text">Yeah the armrest broke after just a week</blockquote>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="turn__expect">
            <span class="turn__who">The agent:</span>
            <ul>
              <li>Recognizes this as a defect — no further questions needed</li>
              <li>Calls <code>request_return</code> with the order ID and reason</li>
              <li>Returns the return ID, refund amount, and return label link</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Screenshot -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>What it looks like</h2>
        <div class="scenario__screenshot">
          <img src={`${base}images/scenario-reasoning.png`} alt="Slot-filling conversation in the chat UI" />
        </div>
      </section>

      <!-- Why it matters -->
      <section class="scenario__section">
        <h2>Why it matters</h2>
        <div class="value-grid">
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Fuzzy input handling</h3>
            <p>"104-something from April 14" is enough. The agent searches, compares dates and amounts, and deduces the right order without asking the user to be precise.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Minimal questions</h3>
            <p>The agent only asks for what it can't figure out. It doesn't ask for the order number (it found it), the item (there's only one), or the email — just the return reason.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="value-card">
            <h3>Tool-aware reasoning</h3>
            <p>The agent knows <code>request_return</code> needs an order ID and a reason. It gets the ID from the search, and asks the user only for the reason.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Base>

<style>
  .scenario { padding: var(--space-3xl) 0; }
  .back {
    display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 4px;
    font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 500; color: var(--c-text-muted);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }
  .back:hover { color: var(--c-primary); }
  .scenario__header { max-width: 680px; }
  .scenario__header h1 { margin-top: var(--space-md); }
  .scenario__lead {
    margin-top: var(--space-lg); font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--c-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .scenario__section { margin-top: var(--space-3xl); }
  .scenario__section h2 { margin-bottom: var(--space-lg); }
  .scenario__section > p {
    color: var(--c-text-secondary); margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .scenario__screenshot {
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border); border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    overflow: hidden; box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
  }
  .scenario__screenshot img { width: 100%; }

  /* ── Turns ── */
  .turn {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background: var(--c-surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
  }
  .turn__label {
    font-size: 0.68rem; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--c-purple);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }
  .turn__who {
    font-size: 0.78rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--c-text-muted);
    text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    display: block; margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
  }
  .turn__you { margin-bottom: var(--space-md); }
  .turn__you .try-prompt {
    background: var(--c-surface-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    padding: var(--space-md);
  }
  .turn__you .try-prompt__text {
    font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--c-text); line-height: 1.6;
    border-left: 3px solid var(--c-primary);
    padding-left: var(--space-md); margin: 0;
  }
  .turn__expect ul {
    padding-left: 20px; margin: 0;
    font-size: 0.88rem; color: var(--c-text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .turn__expect li { margin-bottom: 4px; }
  .turn__expect code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85em;
    background: var(--c-surface-raised); padding: 1px 5px; border-radius: 4px;
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle);
  }

  /* ── Value cards ── */
  .value-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(240px, 1fr));
    gap: var(--space-lg);
  }
  .value-card {
    padding: var(--space-lg); background: var(--c-surface-raised);
    border: 1px solid var(--c-border-subtle); border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }
  .value-card h3 { font-size: 0.95rem; margin-bottom: var(--space-xs); }
  .value-card p {
    font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--c-text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;
  }
</style>
